title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1982-09-15
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 12/2015
description:
Set 1

Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Little Red Rooster, Dupree's Diamond Blues-> Beat It On Down The Line, It Must Have Been The Roses-> Let It Grow-> Day Job

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Touch Of Grey

reviews.review_text: phenomenal I am truly honored to review this show.  It is a master recording of a beautiful Grateful Dead show.  If someone were to ask me, "Hey, Mike, what was it like to be at a Dead show?" --- I figure one of the things I would do is turn to this.  It sounds like a community effort (second set mics on sbd platform?)....etc.  Playing in the Band into Crazy Fingers is an amazing opener and it takes off from there.  Don't miss this.  Touch of Grey is a testament to how very hard these people worked against all of the odds.  Fantastic.  Thank you Brian and crew.
